  The Devonian | Back to Top

   The Devonian period (410 to 360 million years ago) saw a continued diversifiaction of life on
   the land, including the first terrestrial vertebrates, the amphibians, and the first forests of
   trees. In the waters fish continued their diversification with the rise of the lobe-finned and
   ray-finned fish. Invertebrates such as crinoids, coral, and brachiopods thrived in shallow seas
   during the Devonian.

